# Build verification

After changing C++ or library code in this PlatformIO project:

1. Run the build: `pio run` (from project root).
2. Use a timeout that allows the build to finish (e.g. 120 seconds or more); do not assume success after compiling only part of the project.
3. Treat the task as incomplete until the build finishes with **SUCCESS** or you have fixed any reported errors.

This ensures missing symbols (e.g. `selectPressed`), wrong types, and link errors are caught before the user runs the build.
